title: Traumatised Sudan evacuees describe 'horrendous' scenes in Khartoum as they arrive in Cyprus
description: Many people are arriving in Cyprus utterly traumatised and too upset to talk about what they've been through to get here.

title: 'Princess Latifa' posts photo and statement on Instagram account
description: An Instagram profile that appears to belong to Princess Latifa, the Dubai royal who claimed to have been held hostage by her father, has posted a photo and a statement repeating claims that she is "free and living an independent life".

title: This area of Spain could become too hot for tourists - no matter what action is taken
description: By the late afternoon it is uncomfortable to be outside in Seville as the temperatures in Andalucia build towards nearly 40C (104F) at the end of the week.

title: China's Xi calls Zelenskyy for first time since Russian invasion of Ukraine
description: China's Xi Jinping has appealed for Russia and Ukraine to restart peace talks in a phone call with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy - warning "there is no winner in a nuclear war", according to state media.

title: 'Monster' heatwaves, snowpacks and floods: World extreme weather events - and warnings of what's to come
description: Extreme weather is gripping parts of the world amid growing fears this summer could see more record-breaking heat.

title: 'Starvation cult' death toll at least 89 after more bodies dug up
description: The number of victims of a suspected starvation cult has risen to at least 89 after more bodies were dug up in a Kenyan forest.

title: Mother accused of killing her four children may be pardoned after 20 years in prison
description: An Australian mother jailed over the death of her four young children could be pardoned after 20 years.

title: Putin critic says he now faces 'absurd' terrorism charges in Russia - and could be jailed for decades
description: Alexei Navalny, the jailed critic of Vladimir Putin, has said he is being investigated on terrorism charges that could see him sentenced to 30 years in prison.

title: Former New Zealand PM Jacinda Ardern to join Harvard
description: Former New Zealand Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern will join Harvard University this year to bring "insights to students" about her experiences as a world leader.

title: Man executed in Singapore over drug smuggling plot - despite opposition from UN
description: Singapore has hanged a man over a cannabis smuggling plot - despite calls from the United Nations to stop the execution.

title: Latest evacuation flights carrying Britons from Sudan expected to land in Cyprus
description: The latest flights carrying British nationals from Sudan are expected to arrive in Cyprus on Wednesday morning, as UK troops prepare to take over the running of the airfield near Khartoum.

title: Socialite mother of Lord Ashcroft's grandkids admits shooting dead police officer
description: Canadian socialite Jasmine Hartin has pleaded guilty to manslaughter by negligence over the shooting of a police superintendent in Belize.
